<%# FAQ Section - Theme-adaptive accordion %>
<section class="py-24 bg-base-100">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-12">
    <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-12 lg:gap-16">
      <%# Left column - Header %>
      <div class="lg:col-span-4">
        <div class="lg:sticky lg:top-24">
          <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 text-primary text-sm font-medium tracking-wide uppercase mb-4">
            <span class="w-8 h-px bg-primary"></span>
            FAQ
          </div>
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-base-content mb-4">Common questions</h2>
          <p class="text-base-content/60 leading-relaxed">
            Everything you need to know about FlukeBase and how it works.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <%# Right column - Accordion %>
      <div class="lg:col-span-8">
        <div class="divide-y divide-base-content/10">
          <%# FAQ 1 %>
          <details class="group py-6 first:pt-0">
            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer list-none">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-base-content pr-8 group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">What is FlukeBase?</h3>
              <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-base-content/5 group-hover:bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center transition-colors">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-base-content/60 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path>
                </svg>
              </span>
            </summary>
            <div class="pt-4 pr-12">
              <p class="text-base-content/70 leading-relaxed">
                FlukeBase is a platform for structured collaboration on projects. It provides tools for project management
                with milestone tracking, collaboration agreements, and time logging. Users can create projects,
                set up agreements with collaborators, and track progress together.
              </p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <%# FAQ 2 %>
          <details class="group py-6">
            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer list-none">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-base-content pr-8 group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">What types of agreements are available?</h3>
              <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-base-content/5 group-hover:bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center transition-colors">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-base-content/60 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path>
                </svg>
              </span>
            </summary>
            <div class="pt-4 pr-12">
              <p class="text-base-content/70 leading-relaxed">
                FlukeBase supports two agreement types: <strong class="text-base-content">Mentorship</strong> for advisory relationships and
                <strong class="text-base-content">Co-founder</strong> for partnership arrangements. Each agreement can specify compensation expectations
                including hourly rates, equity percentages, or hybrid combinations. Agreements go through a negotiation
                process where parties can accept, reject, or counter-offer terms.
              </p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <%# FAQ 3 %>
          <details class="group py-6">
            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer list-none">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-base-content pr-8 group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">Are agreements legally binding?</h3>
              <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-base-content/5 group-hover:bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center transition-colors">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-base-content/60 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path>
                </svg>
              </span>
            </summary>
            <div class="pt-4 pr-12">
              <p class="text-base-content/70 leading-relaxed">
                <strong class="text-base-content">No.</strong> Agreements on FlukeBase are organizational tools for tracking collaboration terms,
                compensation expectations, and progress. They are not legally binding contracts and
                should not be treated as such. If you need legally enforceable agreements, please consult with a
                qualified attorney to draft appropriate legal documents.
              </p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <%# FAQ 4 %>
          <details class="group py-6">
            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer list-none">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-base-content pr-8 group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">How much does FlukeBase cost?</h3>
              <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-base-content/5 group-hover:bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center transition-colors">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-base-content/60 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path>
                </svg>
              </span>
            </summary>
            <div class="pt-4 pr-12">
              <p class="text-base-content/70 leading-relaxed">
                FlukeBase is currently free to use during our development phase. Future pricing models will be
                communicated transparently as the platform evolves.
              </p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <%# FAQ 5 %>
          <details class="group py-6">
            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer list-none">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-base-content pr-8 group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">Can I lead projects and contribute to others?</h3>
              <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-base-content/5 group-hover:bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center transition-colors">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-base-content/60 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path>
                </svg>
              </span>
            </summary>
            <div class="pt-4 pr-12">
              <p class="text-base-content/70 leading-relaxed">
                Yes. FlukeBase has no role restrictions - all users can create their own projects while also
                participating in agreements on other projects. You can be a project owner and a collaborator
                simultaneously across different projects.
              </p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <%# FAQ 6 %>
          <details class="group py-6">
            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer list-none">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-base-content pr-8 group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">How does time tracking work?</h3>
              <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-base-content/5 group-hover:bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center transition-colors">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-base-content/60 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path>
                </svg>
              </span>
            </summary>
            <div class="pt-4 pr-12">
              <p class="text-base-content/70 leading-relaxed">
                Time tracking is tied to project milestones. You can start a timer while working on a specific milestone,
                and the logged time is recorded against that milestone. The interface updates in real-time without page
                reloads. You can also manually add time entries if needed.
              </p>
            </div>
          </details>

          <%# FAQ 7 %>
          <details class="group py-6 last:pb-0">
            <summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer list-none">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-base-content pr-8 group-hover:text-primary transition-colors">What GitHub features are available?</h3>
              <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-base-content/5 group-hover:bg-primary/10 flex items-center justify-center transition-colors">
                <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-base-content/60 group-open:rotate-45 transition-transform duration-200" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                  <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 6v12m6-6H6"></path>
                </svg>
              </span>
            </summary>
            <div class="pt-4 pr-12">
              <p class="text-base-content/70 leading-relaxed">
                Projects can be linked to GitHub repositories to track commits and contributions. This provides
                visibility into development activity and helps correlate code progress with project milestones.
              </p>
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
